31
00:01:28,130 --> 00:01:30,990
=Love is Always Online=

32
00:01:31,020 --> 00:01:33,940
=Episode 15=

33
00:01:33,950 --> 00:01:34,790
Sounds good.

34
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:35,980
Let's tackle the mission first.

35
00:01:37,060 --> 00:01:39,260
I really want that Sun-Moon Bow.

36
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,940
Hurry up, let's go finish the mission.

37
00:01:56,060 --> 00:01:57,340
For Thy Sake, you're here too.

38
00:01:57,340 --> 00:01:58,940
I was just looking for you
for the mission.

39
00:01:59,980 --> 00:02:00,900
Didn't you just

40
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:01,740
go through a breakup?

41
00:02:01,980 --> 00:02:02,940
Why are you back online?

42
00:02:03,380 --> 00:02:05,020
My ex came to see me today.

43
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:06,310
He said he regrets it and

44
00:02:06,540 --> 00:02:07,820
wants me to give him another chance.

45
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,100
You didn't agree, did you?

46
00:02:10,420 --> 00:02:11,730
It's obvious he's just fooling you.

47
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:13,660
I know that isn't a good idea.

48
00:02:14,020 --> 00:02:15,540
But he seemed really sincere.

49
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:17,540
And I started remembering how happy

50
00:02:17,540 --> 00:02:18,380
we were back then.

51
00:02:18,790 --> 00:02:20,580
I told you, you're too easily swayed.

52
00:02:20,580 --> 00:02:21,940
Learn from Xinran.

53
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:23,220
No matter how Zhuang Wei fusses,

54
00:02:23,220 --> 00:02:24,180
she stays unmoved.

55
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:29,540
Hey.

56
00:02:29,540 --> 00:02:30,380
Are you really

57
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:31,850
reconsidering?

58
00:02:32,350 --> 00:02:33,350
Don't do that.

59
00:02:33,780 --> 00:02:34,660
Don't forget what happened

60
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:35,940
when I got back with my ex.

61
00:02:35,940 --> 00:02:36,980
I know.

62
00:02:36,980 --> 00:02:38,260
He even packed up the toothpaste.

63
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:39,180
Not just the toothpaste,

64
00:02:39,620 --> 00:02:41,300
he even took the remaining tissues.

65
00:02:41,860 --> 00:02:43,300
Never get back to your ex.

66
00:02:43,820 --> 00:02:44,980
Can you two stop already?

67
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:47,580
Every time we meet,
it's all about this thing.

68
00:02:47,580 --> 00:02:48,980
Is it that hard to just play a game?

69
00:02:49,620 --> 00:02:50,460
Alright.

70
00:02:50,660 --> 00:02:52,140
We're here to complete the mission.

71
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:53,660
Yeah.

72
00:02:54,380 --> 00:02:55,540
Let's head to the Tianxia Gang.

73
00:02:56,140 --> 00:02:57,340
Why the Tianxia Gang?

74
00:02:57,660 --> 00:02:58,780
There are four of us, right?

75
00:02:58,780 --> 00:02:59,980
Perfect for the mission.

76
00:03:04,020 --> 00:03:05,500
We could use a few extra shields.

77
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:06,840
Wander Wherever seems good.

78
00:03:07,340 --> 00:03:08,660
Isn't that what I'm here for?

79
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:12,360
It's better to have
someone else take the hits.

80
00:03:13,220 --> 00:03:15,260
But the mission
only allows four people in.

81
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:17,100
Why bring so many shields?

82
00:03:19,060 --> 00:03:20,300
I'll find someone skilled.

83
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:22,150
Someone who can heal us.

84
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:24,180
Aren't you

85
00:03:24,180 --> 00:03:25,420
talking about Wen Cheng?

86
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:26,700
Alright, let's do it.

87
00:03:39,780 --> 00:03:40,740
Hey.

88
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:41,620
What brings you here?

89
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:44,820
We want to borrow some people

90
00:03:44,970 --> 00:03:46,100
to tackle the mission.

91
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:48,220
Didn't expect here to be so quiet.

92
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,540
Boss is working overtime.

93
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:52,300
Wen Cheng's been
in a bad mood lately, barely online.

94
00:03:52,780 --> 00:03:53,940
Why is he in a bad mood?

95
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:55,660
Because he...

96
00:03:55,660 --> 00:03:57,600
He got mud on his pants.

97
00:03:58,300 --> 00:03:59,500
Just wash it off then.

98
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:00,580
He already did.

99
00:04:00,940 --> 00:04:01,940
Still wearing a sour face.

100
00:04:02,740 --> 00:04:04,180
Is mud really that hard to clean?

101
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:05,540
It is.

102
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:07,300
Like some feelings.

103
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:08,500
Can't let go no matter how you try.

104
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:10,420
What are you talking about?

105
00:04:10,420 --> 00:04:11,300
I don't get it.

106
00:04:12,980 --> 00:04:14,460
What's wrong with all of them?

107
00:04:14,460 --> 00:04:15,480
Always talking about

108
00:04:15,490 --> 00:04:16,340
going back to exes.

109
00:04:16,340 --> 00:04:17,220
Can't believe it.

110
00:04:19,020 --> 00:04:20,380
I don't think that's what they mean.

111
00:04:20,380 --> 00:04:21,780
You're just being too sensitive.

112
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:25,620
Be honest with me.

113
00:04:25,620 --> 00:04:26,660
Why is he in a bad mood?

114
00:04:27,020 --> 00:04:28,140
Actually,

115
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:29,020
it's because of you.

116
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:30,740
How did I upset him?

117
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:33,470
He said you can't let go of
your connection with Zhuang Wei.

118
00:04:34,060 --> 00:04:35,540
Zhuang Wei is clearly a jerk.

119
00:04:37,180 --> 00:04:38,420
Those were Wen Cheng's exact words.

120
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:39,900
I'm just passing them along.

121
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:41,100
Zhuang Wei is obviously a jerk.

122
00:04:41,660 --> 00:04:43,140
But you act like you're blind to it

123
00:04:43,140 --> 00:04:43,980
and can't see.

124
00:04:45,780 --> 00:04:46,620
Don't glare at me.

125
00:04:47,180 --> 00:04:48,620
He's the one who said all this.

126
00:04:48,620 --> 00:04:51,060
If you two have issues,
just talk face to face.

127
00:04:51,060 --> 00:04:52,160
Why drag me into the middle?

128
00:04:53,140 --> 00:04:54,870
Why would he be upset because of me?

129
00:04:57,340 --> 00:04:58,230
For the same reason as

130
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,860
you worry about him.

131
00:05:00,180 --> 00:05:01,450
I'm not worried about him.

132
00:05:01,450 --> 00:05:02,300
I'm tired.

133
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:03,260
I'm logging off.

134
00:05:09,740 --> 00:05:11,140
Xinran, I'm heading upstairs.

135
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:12,300
Okay.

136
00:05:32,930 --> 00:05:34,780
Is the signal acting up?

137
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:38,020
(Lord of All)

138
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:45,620
Finished work?

139
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:47,620
Yeah.

140
00:05:48,060 --> 00:05:48,900
I miss you.

141
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:53,260
If Xinran and Wen Cheng

142
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:54,980
keep this up,

143
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:57,380
I think their feelings
will just fade away.

144
00:05:59,420 --> 00:06:00,860
They're both too stubborn.

145
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:03,480
Neither admits they need the other.

146
00:06:03,610 --> 00:06:05,100
They think caring means losing.

147
00:06:06,060 --> 00:06:07,020
So what should they do?

148
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:08,980
They need to realize,

149
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:10,900
love isn't about winning or losing.

150
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,130
It's about both winning together.

151
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:14,020
The one who speaks first

152
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:15,220
isn't the weaker one.

153
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:17,860
It's about being willing to take risks.

154
00:06:17,860 --> 00:06:19,380
That's what makes someone brave.

155
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:21,660
You're quite the talker.

156
00:06:23,380 --> 00:06:25,340
Isn't that just common sense?

157
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:27,180
If Wen Cheng were half as brave as me,

158
00:06:27,180 --> 00:06:29,260
they'd be celebrating their
one-month anniversary by now.

159
00:06:30,460 --> 00:06:31,700
Guess I should thank you then.

160
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:33,580
Thank you

161
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:34,620
for being so brave with me.

162
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:36,540
Of course.

163
00:06:39,940 --> 00:06:41,200
You should get some rest now.

164
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:42,740
Stop thinking about them.

165
00:06:43,140 --> 00:06:44,180
If they're meant to be,

166
00:06:44,790 --> 00:06:46,180
they'll be together eventually.

167
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:47,660
Hmm.

168
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:49,020
Worrying won't help anyway.

169
00:06:50,070 --> 00:06:51,030
Good night.

170
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:52,700
Alright, good night.

171
00:07:01,780 --> 00:07:03,090
(Love Psych: Women's Ideal Men)

172
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:04,620
(Things Women Never Told You)

173
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:05,980
(Make People Like You at First Sight)

174
00:07:24,460 --> 00:07:25,300
Xinran.

175
00:07:25,660 --> 00:07:26,580
I'm heading out.

176
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:28,220
Okay. Where are you going?

177
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:33,340
So formally dressed?

178
00:07:33,340 --> 00:07:34,820
Are you meeting his parents?

179
00:07:34,820 --> 00:07:35,700
What parents?

180
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:37,700
Uncle's restaurant just opened.

181
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:39,260
He wants me to cut the ribbon

182
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:40,500
and grab a meal there too.

183
00:07:41,940 --> 00:07:43,380
This isn't another scam, is it?

184
00:07:44,940 --> 00:07:46,460
It's already open.

185
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:48,060
Why don't you believe it?

186
00:07:48,580 --> 00:07:49,860
I want to believe him too.

187
00:07:49,860 --> 00:07:51,380
But your uncle's easily persuaded.

188
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:53,300
I'm just worried
he'll get tricked again.

189
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:56,300
Everyone deserves a second chance,

190
00:07:56,540 --> 00:07:58,100
especially when it's family.

191
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:00,020
Alright, then go ahead.

192
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:01,940
I'll bring some friends over
to support him.

193
00:08:02,740 --> 00:08:04,540
I knew you were still soft inside.

194
00:08:05,140 --> 00:08:06,820
Don't forget to reach out to Wen Cheng.

195
00:08:07,780 --> 00:08:08,620
Ugh.

196
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:22,060
Why did you have time

197
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:23,060
to ask me out for breakfast?

198
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:24,230
I just thought we

199
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:25,540
haven't seen each other in a while.

200
00:08:26,860 --> 00:08:27,980
Come on.

201
00:08:27,980 --> 00:08:28,900
I figured it was about

202
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:30,660
Jianing starting at my company, right?

203
00:08:32,940 --> 00:08:33,780
You know how it is.

204
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:35,340
Jianing

205
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:36,540
hasn't done anything.

206
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:38,060
She can't handle criticism,

207
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:39,100
especially from you.

208
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:41,100
I hope you'll go easy on her

209
00:08:41,540 --> 00:08:42,460
for my sake.

210
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:43,580
Give her more chances.

211
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:45,860
If I really treated her differently

212
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:47,180
like what you said,

213
00:08:47,580 --> 00:08:48,860
I'd be harming her.

214
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:50,540
Have you forgotten?

215
00:08:51,020 --> 00:08:53,060
When you first started
your internship here,

216
00:08:53,770 --> 00:08:55,020
because of your background,

217
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:56,580
everyone

218
00:08:56,580 --> 00:08:57,700
looked at you differently.

219
00:08:58,870 --> 00:09:00,660
Do you want Jianing
to go through the same?

220
00:09:03,980 --> 00:09:04,820
You're right.

221
00:09:06,340 --> 00:09:07,180
Don't worry.

222
00:09:07,780 --> 00:09:09,020
I'll treat everyone equally.

223
00:09:09,290 --> 00:09:11,020
If she does well, I'll reward her.

224
00:09:11,020 --> 00:09:11,860
If she doesn't,

225
00:09:11,860 --> 00:09:12,780
I'll have to criticize.

226
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:14,620
Though I'm strict,

227
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:15,620
I believe it's

228
00:09:15,620 --> 00:09:16,620
for her own good.

229
00:09:17,940 --> 00:09:19,460
I'm counting on you to help Jianing.

230
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:21,780
This meal's on me.

231
00:09:21,780 --> 00:09:23,900
I hope she can understand

232
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:25,780
what you've done for her.

233
00:09:26,540 --> 00:09:27,380
Ancheng,

234
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:29,020
lately,

235
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,900
how's it going with Jianing?

236
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:32,700
It's alright.

237
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:33,620
How about your job?

238
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:34,460
Is it going smoothly?

239
00:09:34,630 --> 00:09:35,620
Just the usual.

240
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:37,740
Excuse me.

241
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,260
How's the food so far?

242
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:41,020
Mr. Shi,

243
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:42,300
your dishes are amazing!

244
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:43,740
Absolutely.

245
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:44,820
I never eat carrots,

246
00:09:45,180 --> 00:09:47,220
but I could eat a whole pound
of the ones

247
00:09:47,220 --> 00:09:48,060
in your braised brisket.

248
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:49,380
Thank you, thank you.

249
00:09:49,820 --> 00:09:51,660
I personally check all the ingredients.

250
00:09:52,420 --> 00:09:53,420
Last time, I found

251
00:09:53,420 --> 00:09:55,180
worms in some carrots,

252
00:09:55,180 --> 00:09:56,060
so I threw out

253
00:09:56,060 --> 00:09:57,180
the entire batch,

254
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:58,780
just to make sure you all eat well.

255
00:09:59,980 --> 00:10:01,500
Please enjoy, take your time.

256
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,140
Yuan,

257
00:10:06,580 --> 00:10:07,620
is the food enough?

258
00:10:07,620 --> 00:10:08,940
It's great, no need for more.

259
00:10:09,940 --> 00:10:10,860
Uncle.

260
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:13,100
I heard you say earlier,

261
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:15,180
some of that batch had issues,

262
00:10:15,580 --> 00:10:17,100
so you discarded all of them?

263
00:10:17,660 --> 00:10:19,060
Isn't that a bit wasteful?

264
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:21,100
I only want the customers

265
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:21,980
to eat healthily.

266
00:10:24,780 --> 00:10:25,620
Boss.

267
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:27,020
Perfect timing.

268
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:27,860
Let me introduce you.

269
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:29,420
This

270
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,380
is my niece,

271
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:31,220
Yao Yuan.

272
00:10:31,460 --> 00:10:32,300
He's our store manager.

273
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:33,660
I spent a fortune to poach him

274
00:10:33,660 --> 00:10:35,020
from a high-end restaurant.

275
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:37,500
- Hello.
- Hello, hello.

276
00:10:37,980 --> 00:10:39,060
What's up? Need something?

277
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:40,260
Boss, over there.

278
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:42,180
We just got a new batch of potatoes.

279
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:48,900
Hello, Mr. Jiang.

280
00:10:49,540 --> 00:10:50,460
Anlan.

281
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:52,660
Anlan.

282
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:54,180
Today's my first day at work.

283
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:55,580
Could you show me around

284
00:10:55,580 --> 00:10:56,980
so I'd get familiar with the place?

285
00:10:57,660 --> 00:10:59,900
Didn't you intern here before?

286
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,380
You even learned to make coffee
and use the printer.

287
00:11:02,740 --> 00:11:04,100
How could you not know this place?

288
00:11:04,540 --> 00:11:05,380
Oh.

289
00:11:05,540 --> 00:11:06,540
It's a different department.

290
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:08,100
I get shy in new environments.

291
00:11:08,740 --> 00:11:10,980
I need a familiar face to feel at ease.

292
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:14,540
You.

293
00:11:15,570 --> 00:11:17,360
Take her to the planning department.

294
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:18,980
Master.

295
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:21,900
No problem at all.

296
00:11:22,660 --> 00:11:24,000
I said someone familiar.

297
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:24,920
Don't worry.

298
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,410
He can get along with anyone.

299
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:27,860
Please go ahead.

300
00:11:30,020 --> 00:11:30,900
Anlan.

301
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:35,940
I knew you wouldn't want me to go.

302
00:11:36,580 --> 00:11:37,420
You're overthinking it.

303
00:11:37,620 --> 00:11:38,980
I'm assigning your first task.

304
00:11:39,780 --> 00:11:41,260
Sure, mission accepted.

305
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:43,300
One of our partner companies

306
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:44,900
is about to launch a new makeup line.

307
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:47,140
Go interview young people on the street

308
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:48,500
and see what their views are

309
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:49,460
on cosmetics.

310
00:11:49,940 --> 00:11:50,860
Got it.

311
00:11:51,340 --> 00:11:52,180
What kind of task is it?

312
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,220
Why do I not have

313
00:11:53,220 --> 00:11:54,060
any assignments?

314
00:11:54,550 --> 00:11:55,420
How come I didn't know?

315
00:11:55,430 --> 00:11:56,280
Slow down, slow down.

316
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:57,300
Hey, don't follow me.

317
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:58,260
No, no.

318
00:11:58,260 --> 00:11:59,220
Don't I have any assignments?

319
00:11:59,220 --> 00:12:00,460
I'm going to look for some info.

320
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:01,620
Don't follow me.

321
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:02,940
No need, no need.

322
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:17,100
When will you learn to be polite?

323
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:19,180
When you stop asking that, I guess.

324
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:20,020
You wanted to see me?

325
00:12:21,860 --> 00:12:23,380
Chance has changed his mind.

326
00:12:23,380 --> 00:12:24,820
He wants you back to shoot a cover.

327
00:12:24,820 --> 00:12:25,700
Do you want to?

328
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:27,180
Of course I don't.

329
00:12:27,460 --> 00:12:28,300
Okay.

330
00:12:28,580 --> 00:12:30,140
So I refused him for you.

331
00:12:30,420 --> 00:12:32,060
I won't let my people

332
00:12:32,060 --> 00:12:33,620
be ordered around like this.

333
00:12:36,980 --> 00:12:38,200
But I still want to ask you.

334
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:40,340
You've been down lately.

335
00:12:40,340 --> 00:12:41,780
Is it because you lost your job

336
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:43,380
or because the one took your job

337
00:12:43,380 --> 00:12:44,220
was your ex-girlfriend?

338
00:12:45,620 --> 00:12:46,460
How did you find out?

339
00:12:46,940 --> 00:12:48,340
The whole industry knows.

340
00:12:49,020 --> 00:12:50,180
Someone's bound to tell me

341
00:12:50,580 --> 00:12:51,740
anything related to you.

342
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:55,540
Do you think she did it unintentionally?

343
00:12:58,260 --> 00:12:59,780
I want to believe she didn't mean it.

344
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:01,980
But even if she did it on purpose,

345
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:03,380
I don't really care.

346
00:13:04,300 --> 00:13:05,700
Honestly, I'm kind of glad

347
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:07,260
that I can help her.

348
00:13:08,820 --> 00:13:09,660
Jiang,

349
00:13:10,180 --> 00:13:11,260
do you think I'm crazy?

350
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:18,260
Decline any future cases

351
00:13:18,260 --> 00:13:19,100
related to her for me.

352
00:13:19,820 --> 00:13:20,740
Out of sight, out of mind.

353
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:23,660
Do you really think

354
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:25,060
that will solve anything?

355
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:26,700
Even if you don't see her,

356
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:27,700
she's still on your mind.

357
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:28,620
That's even worse.

358
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:32,740
Let's go.

359
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:35,540
Where to?

360
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:36,540
Get some fresh air.

361
00:13:47,060 --> 00:13:47,980
Hey, Jiang.

362
00:13:47,980 --> 00:13:48,820
Yeah.

363
00:13:49,140 --> 00:13:50,660
Coming to the river now usually means

364
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:52,740
we're either confessing or fighting.

365
00:13:53,580 --> 00:13:54,700
You just treat me to a popsicle?

366
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:58,380
Do you still have feelings for Cui Xi?

367
00:13:59,860 --> 00:14:00,940
Feelings?

368
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,140
Honestly, I'm not sure.

369
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:05,380
Does love turn to hate,

370
00:14:05,380 --> 00:14:06,460
or hate turn back to love?

371
00:14:08,340 --> 00:14:10,060
Maybe it's both love and hate at once.

372
00:14:10,060 --> 00:14:11,740
Human emotions are complicated.

373
00:14:12,780 --> 00:14:13,860
If you feel this emotion

374
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:15,220
is affecting your work,

375
00:14:15,220 --> 00:14:16,060
tell me.

376
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:17,100
I'll help you resolve it.

377
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:26,060
Whether you like someone or not,

378
00:14:26,420 --> 00:14:28,060
don't go bothering Yao Yuan anymore.

379
00:14:31,180 --> 00:14:33,020
I wondered why you were so nice today.

380
00:14:34,420 --> 00:14:35,780
It's because you looked so pitiful.

381
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:39,820
Jiang.

382
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:42,460
You're the kind of person

383
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:43,820
who seems annoying at first glance,

384
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:46,460
but deep down, you're quite endearing.

385
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:50,720
Having a boss like you

386
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:52,300
is pretty fortunate.

387
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,100
Then hurry up and

388
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:57,060
earn me a few more popsicles.

389
00:15:10,820 --> 00:15:12,220
(Market Survey Report Writing Tips)
Questionnaires

390
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:13,540
are divided into paper-based

391
00:15:13,540 --> 00:15:15,380
and online surveys

392
00:15:15,380 --> 00:15:16,500
by medium.

393
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:18,740
Oh dear.

394
00:15:19,020 --> 00:15:20,180
Who actually cares about this?

395
00:15:22,260 --> 00:15:23,380
You're way off here.

396
00:15:23,940 --> 00:15:25,980
Surveys are about
real hands-on experience.

397
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:27,500
(Market Survey Report Writing Tips)
What you found online

398
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,900
will only mess things up.

399
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:30,820
How do you know?

400
00:15:32,060 --> 00:15:33,740
I've done a few odd jobs before.

401
00:15:34,020 --> 00:15:35,020
So I have some experience.

402
00:15:37,660 --> 00:15:38,620
If you don't need my help,

403
00:15:38,620 --> 00:15:39,460
I'm heading out.

404
00:15:40,780 --> 00:15:41,700
Hey, wait.

405
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:46,580
How about you come with me?

406
00:15:46,940 --> 00:15:48,820
You just need to watch over me.

407
00:15:49,180 --> 00:15:50,140
Who knows what could happen

408
00:15:50,140 --> 00:15:51,020
if I go alone?

409
00:15:52,540 --> 00:15:53,740
A girl as pretty as you

410
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:54,580
walking down the street

411
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:56,060
could be really dangerous.

412
00:15:56,540 --> 00:15:58,140
Alright, I'll go with you.

413
00:16:06,180 --> 00:16:07,020
Come on.

414
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:09,100
- What?
- Let me show you how.

415
00:16:09,460 --> 00:16:10,340
No need.

416
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:14,780
Hello, I'm with Ruishi.

417
00:16:18,850 --> 00:16:19,700
Sorry to bother you.

418
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:20,700
I'm a Ruishi employee.

419
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:21,540
We don't need it.

420
00:16:26,740 --> 00:16:28,460
Sorry, I'm with Ruishi.

421
00:16:32,180 --> 00:16:33,590
Hello, I'm from Ruishi.

422
00:16:33,590 --> 00:16:34,430
No, no.

423
00:16:35,820 --> 00:16:37,740
The phone never even rang.

424
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:38,580
Stop pretending.

425
00:16:42,020 --> 00:16:43,740
Come on, give it here.

426
00:16:44,740 --> 00:16:45,900
Let me tell you,

427
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:47,620
time is the best teacher.

428
00:16:48,620 --> 00:16:49,700
Now I can

429
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:51,460
easily tell who will stay,

430
00:16:51,460 --> 00:16:52,420
and who will leave.

431
00:16:52,420 --> 00:16:53,260
Seriously?

432
00:16:53,540 --> 00:16:54,380
Look over there.

433
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:57,860
Hello.

434
00:16:57,860 --> 00:17:00,140
Can I ask you to fill out a quick survey?

435
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:01,500
I don't really want to.

436
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:10,340
There's someone there.

437
00:17:10,340 --> 00:17:11,180
This will definitely work.

438
00:17:15,340 --> 00:17:16,260
Hi.

439
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:17,380
Do you have a few minutes

440
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:18,620
to answer a few questions?

441
00:17:19,020 --> 00:17:20,460
Because I think your makeup today

442
00:17:20,460 --> 00:17:21,460
is especially beautiful.

443
00:17:21,730 --> 00:17:22,580
So I want to ask you

444
00:17:22,580 --> 00:17:23,540
beauty-related questions,

445
00:17:23,540 --> 00:17:25,180
is that okay?

446
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:26,740
Sure, now's fine.

447
00:17:27,410 --> 00:17:28,260
Great!

448
00:17:28,260 --> 00:17:30,260
I've been standing there forever
without anyone stopping.

449
00:17:30,260 --> 00:17:31,900
Come on, take a look.

450
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:33,980
Just these few questions.

451
00:17:40,180 --> 00:17:41,020
Okay.

452
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:42,260
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

453
00:17:42,260 --> 00:17:43,180
Thank you so much.

454
00:17:43,420 --> 00:17:44,260
Bye.

455
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,940
Bye.

456
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:49,540
See that?

457
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:52,220
Don't worry.

458
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:53,940
The more time you spend on it,

459
00:17:54,220 --> 00:17:55,340
you'll get as good as me.

460
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:57,900
Hey, where exactly are you from?

461
00:17:58,420 --> 00:17:59,420
I'm still a student.

462
00:17:59,780 --> 00:18:00,700
Hey, Zhang He,

463
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:01,820
let me take you out to eat.

464
00:18:01,820 --> 00:18:02,980
Consider it a thank you.

465
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:04,860
You want to treat me to dinner?

466
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:06,820
No need, but...

467
00:18:07,380 --> 00:18:08,300
Come on, let's go.

468
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:09,440
Then we'll get back to work.

469
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:10,500
Alright.

470
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:17,220
(Heart Is Rotting)

471
00:18:17,220 --> 00:18:18,580
Mr. Wen Cheng.

472
00:18:18,580 --> 00:18:19,980
Can you tell me

473
00:18:19,980 --> 00:18:22,020
why the man I like have kissed me

474
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:23,620
but we still never ended up together?

475
00:18:36,340 --> 00:18:40,780
(Xinran)

476
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:46,620
(Ghosts of Exes)
Made me cry. Highly recommended.

477
00:18:49,020 --> 00:18:49,900
This...

478
00:18:50,090 --> 00:18:52,660
Yao Xinran can't still be thinking
about Zhuang Wei, can she?

479
00:19:03,460 --> 00:19:04,380
Hello.

480
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:06,700
What do you mean by sharing that?

481
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,180
Are you still thinking about Zhuang Wei?

482
00:19:08,660 --> 00:19:09,940
What are you talking about?

483
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,020
Who's thinking about him?

484
00:19:12,260 --> 00:19:14,500
If not, don't post such vague stuff.

485
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,340
Gotta go.

486
00:19:18,180 --> 00:19:19,300
Is he nuts?

487
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:23,940
Really like a ghost,

488
00:19:23,940 --> 00:19:24,780
haunting me.

489
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,860
You're just begging for a scolding,

490
00:19:33,860 --> 00:19:34,740
okay?

491
00:19:34,740 --> 00:19:35,580
You deserve it.

492
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:37,140
It's me, Zhang.

493
00:19:38,580 --> 00:19:39,460
Zhang? Oh, it's you.

494
00:19:39,820 --> 00:19:41,220
I thought you were a scammer.

495
00:19:41,220 --> 00:19:42,180
I was ready to scold you.

496
00:19:43,230 --> 00:19:44,100
What's going on?

497
00:19:44,210 --> 00:19:45,340
What do you need from me?

498
00:19:45,650 --> 00:19:47,140
Wanting me to come back, huh?

499
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:48,340
Cheng,

500
00:19:49,340 --> 00:19:50,820
can you come over for a sec?

501
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:03,540
Cheng, you finally showed up.

502
00:20:04,140 --> 00:20:04,980
I've been waiting for you.

503
00:20:05,460 --> 00:20:06,580
What exactly do you want?

504
00:20:07,580 --> 00:20:08,460
Here's the deal.

505
00:20:08,460 --> 00:20:10,380
Last time, you and your friend Yao Xinran

506
00:20:10,380 --> 00:20:11,340
went on the show together.

507
00:20:11,340 --> 00:20:12,500
It went really well.

508
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:13,460
Our investors

509
00:20:13,460 --> 00:20:14,500
really liked that.

510
00:20:14,820 --> 00:20:15,780
They said

511
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:17,350
they want you and Yao Xinran

512
00:20:17,820 --> 00:20:19,540
to do a special episode or something.

513
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:21,460
Are you willing?

514
00:20:30,050 --> 00:20:31,780
How could you bear to fire Ashley?

515
00:20:33,660 --> 00:20:35,020
Sometimes you have to.

516
00:20:36,380 --> 00:20:37,340
The higher-ups said

517
00:20:37,340 --> 00:20:38,420
she has no click-through rate.

518
00:20:39,420 --> 00:20:40,440
If I don't fire her,

519
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:42,420
I'll be the one getting fired.

520
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:43,860
Look at you.

521
00:20:43,860 --> 00:20:44,780
Just for a pretty face,

522
00:20:44,780 --> 00:20:45,940
you would risk everything.

523
00:20:46,460 --> 00:20:47,660
Good thing you realized it

524
00:20:47,660 --> 00:20:49,100
and called me back.

525
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:51,700
Cheng, you were right to scold me.

526
00:20:51,700 --> 00:20:52,860
I can't do this without you.

527
00:20:52,860 --> 00:20:53,700
Is that okay?

528
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:56,940
Listen,

529
00:20:56,940 --> 00:20:58,620
don't think I'll always come back.

530
00:20:58,620 --> 00:21:00,300
If I didn't still care about this show,

531
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:01,660
I'd still have a smooth life

532
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:03,220
somewhere else.

533
00:21:03,980 --> 00:21:05,620
I know that, Cheng.

534
00:21:05,620 --> 00:21:06,500
Please tell me.

535
00:21:06,980 --> 00:21:08,140
What will make you come back?

536
00:21:11,820 --> 00:21:12,860
It's simple.

537
00:21:13,140 --> 00:21:13,980
First,

538
00:21:14,340 --> 00:21:15,420
this place is far,

539
00:21:15,420 --> 00:21:17,180
so I need a dedicated car
for all my trips.

540
00:21:17,580 --> 00:21:19,220
Second, before and after filming,

541
00:21:19,220 --> 00:21:21,060
I want a cup of black coffee, no sugar.

542
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:22,380
Third,

543
00:21:22,380 --> 00:21:24,060
my suits must be sponsored by brands.

544
00:21:24,060 --> 00:21:25,780
Fourth, I want two assistants

545
00:21:25,780 --> 00:21:27,460
for back massages and shoulder rubs.

546
00:21:27,460 --> 00:21:28,300
How about that?

547
00:21:28,540 --> 00:21:29,420
This is... really...

548
00:21:33,060 --> 00:21:34,060
I'm just kidding.

549
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:35,540
What I want is

550
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:37,220
your absolute respect from now on.

551
00:21:40,820 --> 00:21:42,340
Got it, Cheng.

552
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:52,740
(Celebrity Insights)

553
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:58,460
This is bad.

554
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,100
I just snapped at her.

555
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,620
How do I even bring it up now?

556
00:22:20,940 --> 00:22:21,780
What's wrong?

557
00:22:22,620 --> 00:22:23,700
Why are you sighing?

558
00:22:28,540 --> 00:22:30,220
Being so quiet isn't like you.

559
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:32,700
Is it about your love life again?

560
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:36,020
The ex-girlfriend you

561
00:22:36,020 --> 00:22:36,980
stargazed with?

562
00:22:40,660 --> 00:22:42,380
She's not the type
to think about others much.

563
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:46,140
Yet you still care about her a lot.

564
00:22:51,390 --> 00:22:52,250
Do I?

565
00:22:52,780 --> 00:22:53,780
If you didn't care,

566
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:55,900
you wouldn't be so troubled.

567
00:22:57,660 --> 00:22:58,540
Su Wen,

568
00:22:59,660 --> 00:23:00,660
sometimes,

569
00:23:00,660 --> 00:23:01,500
people depend on others

570
00:23:02,540 --> 00:23:03,780
because the other person

571
00:23:04,220 --> 00:23:05,380
also is dependent.

572
00:23:07,380 --> 00:23:08,940
Although she was wrong,

573
00:23:09,220 --> 00:23:10,220
think about it this way,

574
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:13,220
you actually allowed it,

575
00:23:13,220 --> 00:23:14,060
didn't you?

576
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:18,340
Just like Anlan,

577
00:23:19,180 --> 00:23:21,430
he was always very proactive with me,

